        {
            "review_id": "225288339",
            "steam_id": "76561198090035456",
            "playtime_minutes": 1367,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "It's a good roguelite and it was fun clearing the story and some \"post-game\" stuff. It's a bit hard for me to pinpoint why I didn't enjoy it enough to want to continue after the main story but the one thing that does come to mind is that I didn't really feel much of a \"rush\" playing the game, something which I look for in platforming roguelites.\r\n\r\nWhat I liked:\r\n- There's a certain charm to the characters that draws parallels to manhwas (Korean devs & publisher so maybe that's why)\r\n\r\nWhat I didn't enjoy:\r\n- UI and Description text was kinda confusing during the first few hours\r\n- Boss intro cutscenes feel so slow especially when doing consecutive runs (skip or fast-forward would've been nice) and even saving prisoners where you have to go through dialogue for rewards feels slow"
        },
        {
            "review_id": "225443907",
            "steam_id": "76561198063472983",
            "playtime_minutes": 3326,
            "voted_up": false,
            "votes_up": 1,
            "weighted_score": 0.497925341129303,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "I really like this game, got like 50 hours into it. From all the skulls and builds you try out in future runs, DLC added four awesome skulls and a damn near broken legendary skull. Its charm reminds me of Dead Cells though not as wacky in some areas, it's more serious in tone. Honestly, if you love roguelikes that offer a good challenge to the player plus bonus content after beating the main story, you're gonna love this.\n\nThe only thing that consistently hampers my enjoyment of this game is the crashing. I'm talking about five crashes, some of them I can't even get through one room without the game ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ the bed. Which is my main reason for not recommending it."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226524204",
